body:
**Description**
On my AMD laptop with Radeon HD 7600M/7640G the SKCanvas.Clear() draws my SKGLControl with much lighter color. SKControl behaves correctly. Drivers are up-to-date.
It looks like, that on NVIDIA machines everything works fine.

What can it be?

**Code**

```
        protected override void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintGLSurfaceEventArgs e)
        {
            base.OnPaintSurface(e);

            var surface = e.Surface;
            var surfaceWidth = e.BackendRenderTarget.Width;
            var surfaceHeight = e.BackendRenderTarget.Height;

            var canvas = surface.Canvas;

            canvas.Clear(new SkiaSharp.SKColor(128, 128, 128, 255));

            canvas.Flush();
        }
```

**Actual Behavior**
Photoshop says: 
The color of the control is (188, 188, 188)

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  1.68
- IDE:  Visual Studio
- Platform Target Frameworks: 
  - Windows Classic:  Windows 10

**Screenshots**

![skglcontrol-radeon-clearbug](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1189037/51404113-bf2a4f00-1b52-11e9-8a74-b520086222bd.PNG)

> VS bug [#782038](https://devdiv.visualstudio.com/DevDiv/_workitems/edit/782038)
